2 Grammar of Graphics

The grammar of graphics is a framework which follows a layered approach to describe and construct visualizations or graphics in a structured manner. It was introduced by Leland Wilkinson and has inspired the development of the ggplot2 package in R. In this course, we will often use the ggplot2::ggplot() to create graphs.

ggplot2 is a system for declaratively creating graphics, based on The Grammar of Graphics. You provide the data, tell ggplot2 how to map variables to aesthetics, what graphical primitives to use, and it takes care of the details
